The paper deals with object detection tasks using sensor data fusion, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of neural networks for object detection also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the fusion architectures in adverse weather conditions, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
